Mario Adventure doesn't even work on a NES.  It has major glitches from misuse of the IRQ counter (displays sprites from the wrong pattern table, causing the counter to clock extra times), so the status bar appears too high in the screen, and moves up and down as sprites enter and leave.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Fri May 25, 2007 12:29 pm</p><hr />
